==Old English==
===Etymology===
From West Germanic ''*iwiz'', from Germanic ''*izwiz'', from Indo-European ''*wes''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[ju]], Old Saxon [[ju]] (Dutch [[u]]), Old High German [[iu]] (German [[euch]]), Old Norse [[yðr]], Gothic [[𐌹𐌶𐍅𐌹𐌶]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /e:ow/

===Personal pronoun===
'''ēow'''
# [[you]]: accusative/dative plural form of [[þu|þū]]

